label: content
definition: A single physical entity inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's quantities or qualities.

label: gross
definition: Gains prior to deduction of losses; pre-deducted value (gross), post-deducted value (net).

label: abundance
definition: The degree of quantity of an entity.

label: median
comment: In STATO has a different name: center value

label: standard error
comment: In STATO has a different name: standard error of the mean

label: potential density
definition: A density which would inhere in a bearer if such bearer were adiabatically brought to a standard reference pressure.

label: electrical resistivity
editors note: TO ADD to PATO inverse of conductivity see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Electrical_resistivity_and_conductivity

label: potential temperature
definition: A temperature which would inhere in a bearer if such bearer were adiabatically compressed from it's existing temperature and pressure to a standard presure.

label: turbidity
editors note: TO ADD TO PATO High priority.

label: uptake
definition: The incorporation in a living organism of chemicals and substances from the environment, which can be evaluated by measuring their accumulation.
